### Kali Linux
**Important**: Kali Linux uses externally-managed Python environments, so you must use a virtual environment:
```bash
# Update package lists
sudo apt update
# Install Python and pip (if not already installed)
sudo apt install python3 python3-pip git
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/subtakeover.git
cd subtakeover
# Install required packages
sudo apt install python3 python3-pip python3-venv git
# Clone the repository (replace 'yourusername' with your GitHub username)
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/subtakeover.git
cd subtakeover
# Create and activate virtual environment (REQUIRED on Kali)
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate
# Install Python dependencies
pip3 install -r deps.txt
# Optional: Create alias for easier access
echo 'alias subtakeover="python3 /path/to/subtakeover/subtakeover.py"' >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc
pip install -r deps.txt
# Test installation
python subtakeover.py --help
# Optional: Create activation script for easier access
echo '#!/bin/bash
cd /path/to/subtakeover
source venv/bin/activate
python subtakeover.py "$@"' > ~/bin/subtakeover
chmod +x ~/bin/subtakeover
```
**Note**: Always activate the virtual environment before using the tool:
```bash
cd subtakeover
source venv/bin/activate
python subtakeover.py -d example.com
```
